
[1]periwig

   PER'IWIG, n. A small wig; a kind of close cap formed by an intertexture
   of false hair, worn by men for ornament or to conceal baldness.
   Periwigs were in fashion in the days of Addison.

   PER'IWIG, v.t. To dress with a periwig, or with false hair, or with any
   thing in like form.
